  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Silicon photonics design engineer",
  "description": "<p>Job Scope</p><p>We are looking for motivated talents to join our team in developing cutting-edge silicon photonics devices. The responsibilities include:</p><p>1. Device Development: Design and develop high-performance passive and active silicon photonics devices (e.g., couplers, splitters, polarization splitters/rotators, MUX/DEMUX, phase shifters, photodetectors, modulators, etc.) for optical transceivers, co-packaged optics, and optical switches.</p><p>2. Process Innovation: Collaborate with industrial silicon photonics foundries to co-develop innovative process flows for next-generation photonic devices.</p><p>3. Device Simulation: Perform comprehensive device simulations and build numerical models to predict device performance.</p><p>4. Layout Design: Create tape-out layouts for foundries and follow up to ensure timely delivery.</p><p>5. Testing & Optimization: Conduct detailed optical and electrical testing, perform root cause analysis, and iteratively enhance device performance.</p><p>6. Team Contribution: Play a key role in the design and development of large-scale photonic integrated circuits (PICs).</p><p>Requirements</p><p>We are seeking candidates with the following qualifications:</p><p>1. Educational Background: PhD in Electrical Engineering or related fields, with strong research experience in silicon photonics.</p><p>2. Additional Expertise: Experience in quantum photonics or optical computing is a plus.</p><p>3. Industry Experience: Experience with tape-out processes in photonic foundries and familiarity with photonic PDKs.</p><p>4. Technical Proficiency: Skilled in simulation tools such as Lumerical MODE, FDTD, CHARGE, Ansys HFSS, and Silvaco.</p><p>5. Programming Skills: Proficient in Python and MATLAB for modeling and data analysis.</p><p>6. Communication: Strong communication skills, with fluency in English and/or Chinese.</p><p>7. Team Player: Proven ability to work effectively in a collaborative team environment.</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
